{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow sentence reductions for rehabilitated Extended Determinate prisoners -EDS-",
        "additional_details": "People serving Extended Determinate Sentences can complete rehabilitation programmes, education and their sentence plans while maintaining good behaviour, yet still have no opportunity for earlier release. We believe the justice system should recognise genuine reform. Allowing sentence reductions or earlier review for those who demonstrate sustained rehabilitation could encourage positive behaviour, support reintegration into society and maintain public safety through proper risk assessment.",
        "background": "We want the Government to review Extended Determinate Sentences (EDS) and allow sentence reductions for prisoners who demonstrate sustained good behaviour and rehabilitation. Any changes should apply to those currently serving EDS as well as future sentences.",
